<subSubSection id="C319654DFFFCFF97FEB1F961FECA563C" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFFCFF97FEB1F961FECA563C" blockId="9.[192,1440,1700,1897]" lastBlockId="11.[192,1440,214,345]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFFCFF95FEB1F961FE995187" box="[256,340,1736,1762]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">CHILE</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFFCFF95FED3F961FDFF5187" box="[354,562,1736,1762]" country="Chile" name="Araucania" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Araucanía Region</collectingRegion>
, Cautín Province, Pucón, Huerguehue National Park; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFFCFF95FB18F96EFABA5187" box="[1193,1399,1735,1762]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" value="2021-02-25">25 February 2021</date>
; G. Andrés. Host: Unidentified species (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFCFF95FDD1F940FCC45061" authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1878" box="[608,777,1769,1796]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anyphaenidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. The first photograph shows 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFCFF95FA3DF943FEEA5040" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFCFF95FA3DF943FEEA5040" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">S. striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
standing over the paralyzed ghost spider as it laid on the ground, ventral side upward, grasping its left forecoxa with her mandibles. The second photograph shows 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFCFF95FCEBF884FC285023" baseAuthorityName="Spinola" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[858,997,1836,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFCFF95FCEBF884FC285023" box="[858,997,1836,1863]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">S. xanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pulling the spider in the opposite direction of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFCFF95FEA0F8E7FE5F500D" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="1985" box="[273,402,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFCFF95FEA0F8E7FE5F500D" box="[273,402,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">S. striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, grasping the trochanter of the third left leg with her mandibles, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFCFF95FB19F8E7FAE4500D" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="1985" box="[1192,1321,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFCFF95FB19F8E7FAE4500D" box="[1192,1321,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">S. striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grasps the spider’s right forepatella or forefemur with her mandibles. The third photograph shows the two wasps grappling atop the spider while it laid, ventral side upward, on the ground with 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFEFF97FC65FF50FBAC5676" baseAuthorityName="Spinola" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[980,1121,249,275]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFEFF97FC65FF50FBAC5676" box="[980,1121,249,275]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">S. xanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
attempting to sting and bite 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFEFF97FF70FEB5FE8E5653" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="1985" box="[193,323,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFEFF97FF70FEB5FE8E5653" box="[193,323,284,310]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">S. striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with her mandibles. The 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFFEFF97FDD2FEB5FD285653" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="1985" box="[611,741,284,310]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Sphictostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFFEFF97FDD2FEB5FD285653" box="[611,741,284,310]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">S. striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is grasping the patella of the spider’s second right leg (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFFEFF97FAFDFEB5FF36563C" author="Andres G." pageId="11" pageNumber="10" refId="ref21004" refString="Andres G. 2021. Batalla. Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / fotografiasgerald / with / 50991254266 /. (Last accessed 14 April 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Andrés 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
